    • Constructor Detail

      • BASS_MIXER_NODE

        public BASS_MIXER_NODE()
        Create an object that holds a null BASS_MIXER_NODE.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          BASS_MIXER_NODE obj = new BASS_MIXER_NODE();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new BASS_MIXER_NODE, use the static "constructor" : 
          BASS_MIXER_NODE obj = BASS_MIXER_NODE.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

    • Method Detail

      • asBASS_MIXER_NODE

        public static BASS_MIXER_NODE asBASS_MIXER_NODE(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a BASS_MIXER_NODE object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a BASS_MIXER_NODE object.

      • allocate

        public static BASS_MIXER_NODE allocate()
        Allocate a new BASS_MIXER_NODE.
        The call isNull() on the object created will return false.
          BASS_MIXER_NODE obj = BASS_MIXER_NODE.allocate();
  (obj == null) <=> obj.isNull() <=> false
